SIMPLE: traveler
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Traveler
<hw>Trav"el*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Written also
<ets>traveler</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who travels; one who
has traveled much.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A commercial agent who travels for the purpose of
receiving orders for merchants, making collections, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>A traveling crane. See under
<er>Crane</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Spinning)</fld> <def>The metal loop which travels
around the ring surrounding the bobbin, in a ring spinner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>An iron encircling a rope, bar,
spar, or the like, and sliding thereon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Traveler's joy</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>the
<spn>Clematis vitalba</spn>, a climbing plant with white flowers.</cd>
-- <col><b>Traveler's tree</b></col>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <cd>See
<er>Ravenala</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Travel-tainted</ent>⟦br⟧
